<subSubSection lastPageId="38" lastPageNumber="39" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="36.[151,1437,1512,1913]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1625,1649]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Remarks.</emphasis>
This material was labeled as “ 
<typeStatus box="[658,760,1624,1648]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">holotype</typeStatus>
” and provided with a name which seems, however, never to have been published by Strasser. In the 
<collectionCode box="[592,684,1662,1685]" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/91g3-0mnw" name="Naturhistorisches Museum, Wien" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">NHMW</collectionCode>
there is a label “Manuskriptsname” suggesting its unpublished status, from 
<number box="[258,318,1699,1723]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" value="1980.0">1980</number>
. There are two “ 
<typeStatus box="[499,601,1699,1723]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">holotype</typeStatus>
” preparations in the collection: one with gonopods (
<figureCitation box="[1184,1312,1699,1723]" captionStart="FIGURES 84 – 86" captionStartId="39.[151,264,1305,1328]" captionTargetBox="[159,1415,244,1274]" captionTargetId="figure@39.[151,1436,230,1283]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="FIGURES 84 – 86. Megaphyllum species inquirenda, gonopod slide preparations made by Strasser in 1980, labeled as “ holotype ”, from Greece, Andros Island. (84) In situ right gonopods, lateral view; (85) left opisthomere, probaly caudo-lateral view; (86) left promere, anterior view (scale bar: 0.2 mm). Abbreviations: bp: bifurcated process, fl: flagellum, r: ridge, P: promere." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/214884/files/figure.png" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
Figs 
<number box="[1240,1312,1699,1723]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" value="85.0" valueMax="86.0" valueMin="84.0">84–86</number>
</figureCitation>
) and a part of the 
<number box="[222,236,1740,1763]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" value="7.0">7</number>
th body ring, the other with some walking legs and the gnathochilarium. As the trunk of the “ 
<typeStatus box="[1264,1366,1739,1763]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">holotype</typeStatus>
” individual is missing, we cannot describe it here as a new species. The gonopods fit well to the brachyiuline criteria, even to subgenus 
<taxonomicName box="[354,541,1814,1838]" class="Diplopoda" family="Julidae" genus="Omobrachyiulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Julida" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[354,541,1814,1838]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Omobrachyiulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but differ from all other hitherto described species according to the bifurcated process (
<emphasis bold="true" box="[252,280,1850,1875]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">bp</emphasis>
on 
<figureCitation box="[323,453,1851,1875]" captionStart="FIGURES 84 – 86" captionStartId="39.[151,264,1305,1328]" captionTargetBox="[159,1415,244,1274]" captionTargetId="figure@39.[151,1436,230,1283]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="FIGURES 84 – 86. Megaphyllum species inquirenda, gonopod slide preparations made by Strasser in 1980, labeled as “ holotype ”, from Greece, Andros Island. (84) In situ right gonopods, lateral view; (85) left opisthomere, probaly caudo-lateral view; (86) left promere, anterior view (scale bar: 0.2 mm). Abbreviations: bp: bifurcated process, fl: flagellum, r: ridge, P: promere." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/214884/files/figure.png" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
Figs 
<number box="[379,453,1851,1875]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" value="84.5" valueMax="85.0" valueMin="84.0">84–85</number>
</figureCitation>
.) on the opisthomere. Until new, intact individuals are available, we can only refer to it as a species inquirenda.
</paragraph>
